Not a good bagel shop at all. They do not know how to make coffees at all. Asked for a iced coffee light and sweet and it was very dark, the only milk they had was almond milk, and there was literally ONE ice cube in the cup; and the coffee taste bad itself. To make matters worse they didn't even cut my sandwich in half... The ONLY good thing about this bagel shop is that their prices are fairly low compared to other Park Slope bagel shops, but now I know EXACTLY why that is. Low quality and low standards.

Stopped in while I was in Brooklyn I personally really enjoyed it. The place was nice shop with lots of options for bagels. The sesame cream cheese bagel and plain butter bagel were great. Toasted exactly how I asked and very quick. The food guy and cashier we're both really nice. The bagels were fat and fluffy yet still tasted crisp. The flavor was really nice. Coffee was good regular coffee nothing crazy. I would eat them again. The employees were very nice, bagels were full even on Sunday afternoon.

I was here yesterday with my daughter to get a coffee and I find a hair on the half and half milk and I told one of the guys and he said THAT NOT MY HAIR THAT A LADY'S HAIR AND THEY ALL STARTED TO LAUGH.. Unprofessional workers.  I will never come here again.....  I would notify the health department about this situation

Today, we went in, were asked what we wanted to order, I took a moment to check in w/my kid. Then they just ignored us. Done with this location.

By far the sloppiest and untalented group of drugged idiots. I had to repeat my order 6 times and they still got it wrong. Cream cheese was everywhere but inside my bagel. I asked for it to be scooped 3 times and they had no clue what I was asking. They handed it to me without an ingredient I asked for. Plus, it was 3X more expensive than any other bagel place in the area. Unbelievable.
